result.execSummary:
The defendant Jamel L James was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jamel L James in court with attorney Alexis Liggins.  Owen M. Piotrowski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.  
Probation Agent is in court.  Probation Status Review report filed and reviewed.  Defendant is compliant or mostly compliant with probation.  The remaining condition time is stayed.  Court found that further review is not needed.
Probation Review Hearing scheduled for 11-06-2015 at 01:30 pm.
Request for expungement denied by the Court.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense counsel and defendant as to sentencing.

As to Count 1:
Court ordered defendant to serve  9 MONTHS in the House of Correction consecutive to any other sentence; credit for 1 (one) day served.

As to Count 2:
Court ordered defendant to serve  60  DAYS  in the House of Correction; credit for 60 days; TIME SERVED.
- Pay all costs, fees, assessments and surcharges (including the DNA surcharge) during the term of probation ordered as to Count 1.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.  

COURT ORDERS:
-  defendant to provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis if not already done so

As to Count 1:
Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for  2   YEARS  with the following conditions:
Probation may be discharged after 18 months if the terms of probation have been completed successfully

- Court ordered 30 days in the House of Correction; stayed for the use at the discretion of the probation department.
- Attend and successfully complete a Batterer's Intervention program
- Comply with any treatment or programming ordered by probation
- AODA assessment and comply with any recommended treatment
- Absolute Sobriety
- No drugs without a valid prescription
- No contact with the victim without approval of the agent.  Telephone contact is approved
- 3rd party contact for purposes of child visitation as approved by the agent
- Obtain GED/HSD
- Seek/maintain employment.
- Pay all costs, fees, assessments and surcharges (including the DNA surcharge) during the term of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.  
- No contact with firearms
- Attend the probation review hearing on 11-06-215.

Received and filed:  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.

As to the Amended Count 1 and Count 2:
Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the Defendant guilty as to both counts and enters judgment of conviction into the record forthwith. 

Parties are prepared to proceed to sentencing.  Jury trial is vacated.

Defendant Jamel L James in court with attorney Gregory A. Renden.  Defendant Jamel L James in custody.  Benjamin Lindsay appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

State files Amended Information with the court.
Count 1:  Misdemeanor Battery, Domestic Abuse Assessments, a class A misdemeanor, contrary to Wisconsin State Stats. 940.19(1), 939.51(3)(a), 973.055(1)
Count 2:  Disorderly Conduct, Domestic Abuse, a class B misdemeanor, ontrary to Wisconsin State Stats. 947.01(1), 939.51(3)(b), 968.075(1)(a)

Defense counsel waived reading of the Amended Information and entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of defendant.
Clerk:  jms

Request for Substitution of Judge received and filed.  Court consented to substitution against Judge KREMERS.  Parties are advised the Clerk of Circuit Court reassigned case pursuant to current court rules to Judge Dallet, Branch 40.

Attorney Gregory A. Renden in court, defendant Jamel L James not in court, in custody.  Benjamin Lindsay appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Bail motion by defense argued and granted by the Court.  Court adjusted bail down to $500.00 CASH with continued turnover to Justice Point and all conditions previously ordered. Defense counsel requests a Final Pretrial & Jury Trial.  Parties are notified that effective August 1, 2015 this case will be reassigned per rotation to Judge Jeffrey Kremers, Branch 36 in Courthouse room 502.  Final pre-trial scheduled for August 3, 2015 at 01:30 pm.  Jury trial scheduled for August 26, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jamel L James in court with attorney Gregory A. Renden.  Defendant Jamel L James in custody.  Ron Dague for Benjamin Lindsay appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
NO ADA OR DA FILE IN COURT.
Case is called on the record at approximately 10:39 a.m.
State is requesting an adjournment.  Defense Counsel objects, requests a bail modification.
State asks the Court to have the case passed temporarily in order to try and contact the Domestic Violence Unit.
Case is temporarily passed. 

Case is recalled on the record at 11:48 a.m.
Defendant Jamel L James in court with attorney Gregory A. Renden.  Defendant Jamel L James in custody.  Benjamin Lindsay appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
ADA FILE IN COURT.
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the state:Ronald Linzmeyer-MPD Detective.  State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and pleads not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 23.  Scheduling conference scheduled for June 18, 2015 at 08:30 am.  Bail/bond hearing scheduled for June 18, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Signed and filed, No Contact/NO FIREARMS Order.  Defendant to have no contact with KIRA S.
  Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION.

Defendant Jamel L James in court with attorney Gregory A. Renden.  Defendant Jamel L James in custody.  Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  hgj.  Defendant given a copy of complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  Defendant plead not guilty TO MISDEMEANOR COUNT 2.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge GRADY, Branch 23.  Case is adjourned for preliminary hearing in Branch PE FOR BRANCH 23.

  Commissioner advised DNA sample has been obtained from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant he/she may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if he/she meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4).

  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 12, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
Arrest Warrant received from the D.A.'s office on filing date of Criminal Complaint.
